370	To use a Mayer--Vietoris argument on a 2-affine cover, one needs the positive-degree cohomology of each affine piece to vanish. This is Serre's classical theorem on affine schemes. Since a full scheme-level proof is not yet available in the library, we package the vanishing statement as a hypothesis class.
