453	A quasi-compact separated scheme \(X\) over \(k\) admits an open cover by two affines \(U_1, U_2\) whose intersection \(U_1 \cap U_2\) is again affine. Such a cover is the geometric input for the abstract Mayer--Vietoris machine. This section packages the data into a bundled structure and specialises the LES.
